CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 2, 1957, pg. A1 reads: " "Keep Driving For New Members" - That's what Urban League executive A.J. Allen (standing) is telling the kickoff meeting YMCA membership roundup at the Centre Ave. branch, where the first report of the campaign was made. Looking on, from left to right, are James M. Burgette, executive secretary of the Centre Avenue "Y"; William A. Arvin, "big boss" of the campaign, and William W. Goode, "co-big boss." - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: James M. Burgette, William A. Arvin, and William W. Goode, listening to A.J. Allen speak about membership drive in Centre Avenue YMCA
